  "prompt": "Does cctv works during power cut?",
  "response": "CCTV systems typically require power to operate. During a power cut, standard CCTV cameras will not function unless they are supported by backup power solutions. Here are some common methods to ensure CCTV cameras can operate during a power outage:\n\n1. **Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS)**: A UPS can provide backup power to CCTV systems and ensure they continue to operate during a power cut for a limited time, depending on the capacity of the UPS.\n\n2. **Battery-Powered Cameras**: Some CCTV cameras come with built-in batteries or can operate on battery power, allowing them to continue functioning during outages.\n\n3. **Solar-Powered Cameras**: These cameras use solar panels for power and can operate independently of the electrical grid, making them effective in areas prone to power outages.\n\n4. **Backup Generators**: A generator can be used to provide power to the entire CCTV system for extended periods during outages.\n\nIf you rely on CCTV for security, it's a good idea to implement one of these backup solutions to ensure continuous operation during power cuts.",
